commitResults.messageTitle: Implement separate lists and change UI
commitResults.messageBody:
Client and Housekeeper are stored in one general list.

Showing one list in UI does not provide good visualisation, have to use
command list client or list housekeeper to filter out contacts by type,
making it inefficient.

Storing Clients and Housekeepers in two separate lists in the hard disk,
and read from the two lists when startup.

By storing in two separate lists, loading and saving become more
efficient, leading to an improved performance.

Labels are used to differentiate between client and housekeeper. Client
card is storing contact detail and housekeeping detail.

There is no obvious differentiation between client list and housekeeper
list. Client card is storing too much information.

Titling client list and housekeeper list. Splitting client card into two
halves, one half stores contact detail, the other half stores
housekeeping detail.

It is easy to differentiate two lists by title. Separating contact
detail and housekeeping detail makes it tidier.
